      "span_text": "In connection with this, exogenous miRNAs from plants or milk were found in the serum and tissues of mice and humans, for instance, the discovery of the rice specific miR-168a in mouse liver to regulate the expression of low-density lipoprotein receptorassociated protein-I, implying that miRNAs can be transmitted from dietary sources."
